articles.content: People wading through an inundated street in the South Korean city of Gwangju on July 17 following torrential rains. South Korean broadcasters ran videos of severe flooding in Seosan, with water swamping markets and apartment complexes, as well as submerging parked cars. Some 403 schools were closed and 166 reported property damage from the heavy rain, the Ministry of Education said.
